title: Big second half propels FSU to easy win over Louisville
text:
Sports Florida State Seminoles Big second half propels FSU to easy win over Louisville 
PICTURE GALLERY: Check out pictures from the NCAA football game between the Florida State Seminoles and Louisville Cardinals at Doak Campbell Stadium in Tallahassee. Orlando Sentinel 
It took awhile to get going but once Florida State hit its stride on Saturday, it pulled away from Louisville for a 41-21 win. 
The win was the 28th straight in the ACC for the Seminoles. 
FSU trailed the Cardinals 7-6 at the half before scoring touchdowns on the first five drives of the second half to pull away. 
Everett Golson finished with 372 yards on 26-of-38 passing with three touchdowns and no interceptions. 
The Seminoles still do not have an offensive turnover all season long. 
Davlin Cook picked up the pace in the second half too, finishing with 163 yards after only having 29 in the first half. He left the game midway through the fourth quarter after clutching his injured hamstring during a run. 
Cook had two touchdowns rushing. 
Freshman quarterback Lamar Jackson tossed three touchdowns in the loss for Louisville. Jackson, who entered the game with the third-most rushing yards for a freshman in college football, was held to just 32 yards rushing on 19 carries.
